  "prompt": "In SimCity BuildIt, how important is it to build the airport?",
  "response": "In SimCity BuildIt, building the airport is quite important for several reasons:\n\n1. **Tourism and Income**: The airport attracts tourists to your city, which can significantly boost your income. More tourists mean more spending in your shops and businesses.\n\n2. **Trade Opportunities**: The airport allows you to participate in global trade. You can send and receive items from other players, which can help you acquire goods you might be lacking for building and upgrading your city.\n\n3. **Special Events**: The airport often plays a role in various events or challenges, offering opportunities to earn rewards that can benefit your city.\n\n4. **Expansion Potential**: As your city grows, having an airport can provide more expansion options, including unlocking new buildings and services that enhance the overall functionality of your city.\n\n5. **Civic Satisfaction**: Airports contribute to the satisfaction of your citizens since they enjoy the amenities and services that come with increased tourism and global connectivity.\n\nIn summary, while you can progress in the game without the airport, building it can provide numerous benefits that enhance your gameplay experience and efficiency in managing your city. Therefore, it's advisable to prioritize the airport when you can.",
